'''János György Szilágyi''' (16 July 1918 – 7 January 2016) was a Hungarian historian who was a specialist in ancient [[theatre|drama]] and [[Greek art]]. He was born in Budapest.<ref name=Rtt>Ritook, Zsigmond. (1997) [http://epa.niif.hu/01400/01462/00020/pdf/005-015.pdf "The contribution of Hungary to international classical scholarship"], ''[[Hungarian Studies (journal)|Hungarian Studies]]'', 12. Retrieved 12 March 2014. {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6NtepxQmg?url=http://epa.niif.hu/01400/01462/00020/pdf/005-015.pdf |date=2014-03-07 }}</ref> In 2011 he was awarded the [[Order of Merit of the Republic of Hungary]]. He died at the age of 97 in 2016.<ref>[http://magyarmuzeumok.hu/tema/2967_elhunyt_szilagyi_janos_gyorgy Elhunyt Szilágyi János György (Magyarmuzeumok.hu), 2016. január 7.]</ref>

