'''Veit Arnpeck''' (1440-1505) was a [[Bavaria]]n [[historian]] from [[Landshut]]. He was educated at [[Amberg]] and [[Vienna]] and later became [[parish priest]] of St. Martin's Church, Landshut and chaplain to Bishop Sixtus.{{who|date=November 2011}} He is considered a significant figure in the development of Bavarian history and was praised by Aventin as one of his most important predecessors. His works include ''Chronicon Austriacum'' down to 1488 ([[Bernhard Pez|Pez]], Script. rer. Austr., I, 1165), ''Liber de gestis episcoporum Frisingensium'' ([[Martin Deutinger|Deutinger]], Beitr. z. Gesch. d. Erzbisth. Munch.-Fries., III), and the ''Chronicon Baioariorum'' (Pez, Thesaurus, III, ii, 19 sq.).

